You are making the `Collapse` as a [controlled component][1], on click you making the parent render and therefore it doesn&#39;t work as you expect.

If you want to avoid rendering, you need to use the uncontrolled version or wrap it and compose it as uncontrolled.

Refer to [Controlled VS. Uncontrolled][2] in React docs.

You have uncontrolled version in [`reactstrap`][3] docs:

```
import React from &#39;react&#39;;
import { UncontrolledCollapse, Button, CardBody, Card } from &#39;reactstrap&#39;;

const Example = () =&gt; (
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;Button color=&quot;primary&quot; id=&quot;toggler&quot; style={{ marginBottom: &#39;1rem&#39; }}&gt;
      Toggle
    &lt;/Button&gt;
    &lt;UncontrolledCollapse toggler=&quot;#toggler&quot;&gt;
      &lt;Card&gt;
        &lt;CardBody&gt;
          Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Nesciunt magni, voluptas debitis
          similique porro a molestias consequuntur earum odio officiis natus, amet hic, iste sed
          dignissimos esse fuga! Minus, alias.
        &lt;/CardBody&gt;
      &lt;/Card&gt;
    &lt;/UncontrolledCollapse&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
);

export default Example;
```


  [1]: https://reactjs.org/docs/forms.html#controlled-components
  [2]: https://reactjs.org/docs/glossary.html#controlled-vs-uncontrolled-components
  [3]: https://reactstrap.github.io/components/collapse/

